<P><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
<IFRAME FRAMEBORDER=1 ALIGN=CENTER width=100% HEIGHT=200 SCROLLING=YES SRC="http://www.larian.com/ubb/Forum9/HTML/000557.html">
<TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=0 WIDTH="95%"><TR ><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#F0DCA0" FACE="Verdana, Arial">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR background="http://www.larian.com/ubb/forumtextureL.jpg"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Mpemba Effect</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Do you think game balancing DD is impossible? I see theres many posts saying the survivors death scorpion is too strong. Then theres the mages summoned creatures are too weak. The warrior archers elemental skills are hardly worth putting any points since they don't do much more damage than a decent bow.<P>This all makes some combinations impossible. A true summoner or a true survivor is pretty tough. But if these aspects were improved(?) so that these are feesable and the fact that any class can select any skill (of any level). Wouldn't that now make shift the balance so that if one was to select the best skill from each class they'd complete the game even easier than it is already? For example if you could complete the game feesablily as a hacker warrior and also as a summoner mage. Then someone who was to put their points into a hacker and summoner who breeze the game.<P>One way which may help balance is pre-requesits (which I don't think DD has) or perhaps is skill points added in early skill influenced skills nearer to the end of the tree i.e. putting points in an early skill would increase the damage to skill later in the tree. This way theres just not enough level upgrades in the game to be the best of all worlds.<P>So what do you think about DD and balance?  <IMG SRC="http://www.larian.com/ubb/smile.gif"></FONT></TD></TR><TR background="http://www.larian.com/ubb/forumtexture.jpg"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">geldonyetich</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Dragging this old post out of the drink, I realize that it is a no brainer that the death scorpions gained with the "Deadly Gift" ability are too powerful.    <P>However, I've figured out that the death scorpions are not just a little too powerful, they are actually TEN TIMES as powerful as they should be.<P>The problem is simple: Somebody misplaced a decimal point. <P>At skill lvl 1 the "Deadly Gift" skill gives death scorpion lvl 100.  At skill lvl 2  your death scorpion is lvl 200.  At lvl 3, lvl 300, and so on.   <P>More appropriate would be to cut the scorpion lvl down to 1/10th, as that matches the balance philosophy of most other skills in the game.  This makes the scorpions less unstoppable Juggernauts of doom and more like an actual *trap*.<P>That's an obvious mistake, and one that renders the "summoner" mages a joke.    Just something to keep in mind for the patch.<P>As things are in the current version, I really have nothing to fear from any beast in the game.   My death scorpions can destroy anything, and I've got an unlimited supply thanks to my friendly neighborhood thief trap dealer.<P>Divine divinity is a critically acclaimed game, and I think for many deserved reasons, however it's sad to see a bug of this magnitude has been left in the game for as long as it has. <P>Yet, I suppose if I'm that badly offended, there is a simple fix:<BR>Just don't use the scorpions.<P>I still might keep one or two around to release if I'm in a bothersome jam, however  <IMG SRC="http://www.larian.com/ubb/smile.gif">.<BR><p>[This message has been edited by geldonyetich (edited 13-01-2003).]</FONT></TD></TR><TR background="http://www.larian.com/ubb/forumtextureL.jpg"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Rana Loreus</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Well, here's a couple of way to make scorpions less powerful...<P>o Increase the weight of scorpions<BR>o Don't let Tingalf sell scorpions<BR>o All scorpions last only for x time units<P>And off the bats, Enchant is certainly too 'powerful' (when compared to other skills). Embrace Shadows, Pickpocket and such too need some tweaking. </FONT></TD></TR><TR background="http://www.larian.com/ubb/forumtexture.jpg"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">VECTOREFLAME</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Maybe the Larians can consider making the scorpions hostile to both you and enemies in the next patch. (Make a time limit after you plant the scorpion so that the scorp doesn't come after you, like the <A HREF="http://www.larian.com/ubb/Forum16/HTML/002868.html" TARGET=_blank>summoning bug</A>.)</FONT></TD></TR><TR background="http://www.larian.com/ubb/forumtextureL.jpg"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">geldonyetich</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Nothing so minor as that.  Scorpions are TEN TIMES as potent as they should be.   They really need to be nerfed down to 1/10th their potency.<P>ALthough I did have this idea:<P>1. Make them weigh 10 times as much as they do now.<BR>2. Make them cost 100 times as much as they do now.  (About 5000-10000 gold each)<BR>3. Make them never drop off monsters.  Only findable already placed or on a shopkeeper.<P>That would be potentially balanced considering their potency.<BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR background="http://www.larian.com/ubb/forumtexture.jpg"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Rana Loreus</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Or make all scorpions hostile to each other.<P>BTW, all this said, scorpions are useless against Dragon-riders. Perhaps they shall make scorpions weak vs. all elements (a stunned scorpion is less likely to do much damage).<P>The other balance-toppling 'feature' is having Frost on weapons. The simplest thing to do is make it the same as the Freeze spell - it only works against creatures with lesser Spiritual Resistance. <P>Another way is instead of freezing them outlike, make them slower, like as if they are inflicted with the 'limbs of lead' spell.<P>That said, most creatures in the Wastleland has high Spritiual Resistance which is why the Divine skills are useless. I think it shalln't be an outright limitation. For example, Divine Death requires the target to have less than x amount of Spiritual Resistance. Say x is 50, so a creature with a SR (Spiritual Resistance) of 50 has 100% chance of being hit by the spell, a creature with SR of 60 has 50% chance of being hit by the spell and a creature with SR of 70 has 25% and so on...It makes spells more useful without they being really too over-powered.<P>And one thing. Not actually a balance post, but how many of you don't use temporal storm because of the 'earthquake' effects which makes the eyes hurt? <P><p>[This message has been edited by Rana Loreus (edited 14-01-2003).]</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
</IFRAME>
</FONT>
